<span id="freeTextContainer6708720954028488731">Dallaire&apos;s powerful memoir is important, graphic, and undeniable. It is, however, a tough read because of the disturbing events he describes and the even more disturbing lack of action on behalf of Rwanda&apos;s victims. Its historic importance and brutal honesty earns it five stars.</span>
  <span id="freeText6708720954028488731" style="display:none">Dallaire's powerful memoir is important, graphic, and undeniable. It is, however, a tough read because of the disturbing events he describes and the even more disturbing lack of action on behalf of Rwanda's victims. Its historic importance and brutal honesty earns it five stars.</span>
